summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeDiscover Morphe eyeshadows, remastered, with the ChromaPlus 6-Pan Eyeshadow Palette. Powered by a ChromaPlus blend, these all-new shadow formulas deliver pigment-packed performance and all-day wear. Effortlessly build dimension with blendable mattes, shimmers, metallics, and exclusive Molten Metals.
details: DetailsFeatures6 cool-toned neutral eyeshadowsDimension-building mattes, shimmers, metallics & formula-flexing Molten MetalsPersonal application mirror for on-the-go artistryShadesTop Row: Hush Money (matte cream), Champagne Splash (wet/dry sparkling champagne), Taupe Tier (matte taupe)Bottom Row: Stealth Wealth (metallic milk chocolate), Cool Millions (wet/dry graphite), Highbrown (matte rich brown)Research ResultsThe majority of consumers agreed ChromaPlus eyeshadows deliver:Highly pigmented, single-swipe color payoff*Non-patchy, seamless, even application*Silky-smooth, buttery-soft texture*Effortless application**Based on a 21-person consumer perception study.Item 2641284How To UseFor a seamlessly diffused effect, apply matte shades with a fluffy blending brush. For more precise application, such as to line and define your lash lines, apply matte shades with a smaller detail brush.Pack shimmer and metallic shades onto your lids by pressing them on with your fingertip for intense payoff or by using a flat packer brush.Layer different shade finishes to create depth; blend mattes to build your base, press shimmers onto the centers of your lids or inner eye corners for brightness, and top with metallics or Molten Metals for a high-impact finish.IngredientsHush Money: Talc, Mica, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Silica, Magnesium Stearate, Dimethicone, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Octyldodecyl Stearoyl Stearate, Boron Nitride, Phenoxyethanol, Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Magnesium Myristate, Tocopheryl Acetate, Lauroyl Lysine, Hydroxyapatite, Mangifera Indica (Mango) Seed Oil, Caprylyl Glycol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Zinc Oxide, Tin Oxide, Tocopherol. May Contain/Peut Contenir (+/-): Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499).Stealth Wealth: Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Mica, Dimethicone, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Magnesium Stearate, Octyldodecyl Stearoyl Stearate, Talc, Ethylhexyl Palmitate, Silica, Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Boron Nitride, Phenoxyethanol, Vinyl Dimethicone/Methicone Silsesquioxane Crosspolymer, Aluminum Starch Octenylsuccinate, Tocopheryl Acetate, Lauroyl Lysine, Hydroxyapatite, Tin Oxide, Mangifera Indica (Mango) Seed Oil, Caprylyl Glycol, Water (Aqua, Eau), Ethylhexylglycerin, Zinc Oxide, Tocopherol. faceoff_positive.comments:
Morphe's ChromePlus Outer Spice palette has six warm-toned shades: Sugar & Spice, Cinnamon Twist, Ginger Snapped, Sweet Talker, Gold Flavor, and Dash of Cocoa. 
- Sugar & Spice, described as beige, appears to me as a matte light pink. 
- Cinnamon Twist, described as pink champagne in a Molten Metal finish, is a pink metallic glitter. 
- Ginger Snapped, described as mauve, is a matte red brown. 
- Sweet Talker, described as deep rose in a shimmer finish, is a beautiful burgundy. 
- Gold Flavor, described as antique gold in a Molten Metal finish, is a gold metallic glitter. 
- Dash of Cocoa, described as chocolate in a pearlescent matte, is a brown infused with glitter. 

This set is in a mirrored plastic palette, which protects it from damage. Sometimes it protects it too well, as I have difficulty opening it. But I would far prefer that, over a case that opens easily. 

I typically apply all of these at the same time with Sugar & Spice as a base that blends out to Ginger Snapped, with Dash of Cocoa in my crease and outer corner. I then dab the Molten Metals on with my finger, applying Cinnamon Twist to the middle of my lid, and Gold Flavor to the inner corner. I apply Sweet Talker with a liner brush along my lash line. 
Of course, you could also apply these individually, or in various combinations.

Overall, I am enjoying this palette. The pigments are rich when applied over an eyelid primer and the shadows blend together well. I definitely plan to try some of the other palettes in this line.
faceoff_positive.headline: Great eyeshadow! Plan to try the other ChromePlus palettes

faceoff_negative.comments: This palette, for the 6 shadows that you get, is a good value for the price (which I've spotted online is on sale from $15 to $11.50 at Ulta). I would much rather purchase this at a more budget-friendly price point because while the shadows are fun to work with and are easy enough to use, the color story is fun for maybe one or two looks and the shadows do not pack much intensity (despite the emphasis on the "foil" metallics). They are gorgeous in the pan, and the matte shadows that come with them work well when used as a base underneath those foils. Using a wet eyeshadow brush with the foil shades is a must as the shadows tend to become muddy quickly. This palette works better as a quad (the random slightly metallic brown/espresso shade did not fit with the rest of pans). After a few hours of dancing, the shadows halfway held on (as I expected them to). Additionally, I noticed that the eyeshadow cakes were all retracted from the metal pan, so be careful as the shadows are a bit fragile. Overall fun for practice with metallics, and for looks that are summery/mermaidy.
faceoff_negative.headline: Morphe shadows are good, not great
